1.Identifier

------------

1. Identifier is used for identification purpose.
2. Method name, variable name, class name, interface name are nothing but identifier.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ex:-What are the Identifiers in below code.
class Demo 
{
	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		int a=10;
	}
}

Answer:
   1. Demo-->class name 
   2. main-->method name
   3. String-->Pre-define Java class Identifier
   4. args-->variable name
   5. a-->varibale name
   
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#RULES FOR DEFINING JAVA IDENTIFIERS

1. The identifier contains lower case a to z, upper case A to Z, 0 to 9 number, $(dollar) and _ (underscore).

Valid				Invalid
rasul_attar			rasul#
Rasul_123			rasul@


2. Identifier can't start with number. It is start with lower case a to z, upper case A to Z, $ and _

Valid				Invalid
rasul_attar			123_rasul
$rasul				1ab3_xyz
_rasul$attar	

      
3. Identifiers are case sensitive.
Ex
      int rasul=10;
      int Rasul=10;
      int RASUL=10;

     These 3 are different cases and valid.


4. There is no limit and length for java Identifiers
Ex
      int dfhkhdfhdjfhdhfkdhfjdfdjk45646464654dfdfdfdf54564564dfdfdf=10;



5. Reserved Words can't use as Identifies
Ex
    int x=10;
    int if=20;        //if is reserved word
    int for=10;       //for is reserved word
